National Assembly: Questions to the Deputy President, Virtual Meeting Platform, 31st March 2022, 14:00-17:45 PARLIAMENT - The Mineral Resources and Energy department has proposed other measures to replace the temporary R1.50 per litre fuel levy reduction. The measures will replace the fuel levy reduction from June. Fuel Hike | WATCH:Â Warning of possible April increase Finance minister Enoch Godongwana tabled the proposal in the National Assembly on Thursday. Godongwana said, "a broad package of relief measures will be explored and will come into effect after the expiry of the fuel levy reduction ... A reduction in the Basic Fuel Price of 3c/l, in line with the recommendations of the review done by the DMRE. A termination of the Demand Side Management Levy (DSML) of 10c/l on 95 unleaded petrol sold inland." "Interventions will be considered by the DMRE to reduce the price pressure for illuminating paraffin over the medium term."